30/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The prosecutor's office in Belgrade has filed charges against two people accused of attacking prominent journalist Teofil Pancic aboard a public bus last month in Belgrade.
Media reported on Sunday (August 29th) that the pair, arrested in early August, are charged with beating Pancic with metal bars, leaving him with head and arm injuries.
Tomo Zoric, spokesperson of the state public prosecutor's office, said that violence against journalists will not be tolerated.
If convicted, the two suspects could face up to five years in prison.
(Beta, B92, RTS -- 29/08/10)
